706931f-a.title: Brooklyn: Sumner Place - Flushing Avenue
706931f-a.text:
Sumner Pl. near s.e. corner ofFlushing Ave., B'klyn.
Sept. 25, 1341

704394f-b.title: Brooklyn: Flushing Avenue - Sumner Place
704394f-b.text:
(1)
796-800 Flushing Ave., south side, between Sumner Place and Fayette
Street. The house standing back from the street is an extensien of the
Charles De Bevoise heuse (built in 1836) the main portien of which stood
on the site of No. 796. The German branch of the Y.M.C.A., erganized in
1878, purchased the old homestead in 1885 and used it until merged with
the main Williamsburg Y.M.C.A.
About 19221
Eugene L. Armbruster Cellection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(2)
The same, another view.
September 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAd BE REPRODUCED.
